;; Kanban board — full-stack with Docker deploy, Wiggum loop, step-once mode
;;
;; Natural iteration sequence:
;;
;;  Phase 1 — Frontend (React + TypeScript + Vite)
;;   1.  Scaffold: Vite project, deps, test setup
;;   2.  Data model: useKanban hook, Board/List/Card types
;;   3.  Core CRUD: add/rename/delete lists and cards
;;   4.  Drag-and-drop: HTML5 DnD, reorder within + between lists
;;   5.  Frontend tests passing
;;
;;  Phase 2 — Backend (Node.js + Express + SQLite)
;;   6.  Server scaffold: Express + TypeScript, SQLite via better-sqlite3
;;   7.  DB schema + migrations: boards, lists, cards tables
;;   8.  REST API: CRUD endpoints for boards, lists, cards
;;   9.  Wire frontend to API (replace localStorage with fetch calls)
;;   10. Backend + integration tests passing
;;
;;  Phase 3 — Deploy (Podman + podman-compose)
;;   11. Dockerfile: multi-stage build (build frontend, serve via Express)
;;   12. docker-compose.yml: app service + volume for SQLite db file
;;   13. Health check endpoint, graceful shutdown
;;   14. `docker-compose up` starts and all smoke tests pass
;;
;; step-once? true — pauses after every iteration for human review.
;; At the terminal: step / retry / abort
;; In the UI: Continue / Retry / Abort with optional feedback
;;
;; Usage:
;;   clj -M:run graphs/examples/kanban-fullstack-wiggum.edn --project-dir ./my-kanban

{:objective
 "Build and deploy a full-stack Kanban board application.

  === Phase 1: React frontend ===
  - Multiple named lists side-by-side (To Do, In Progress, Done)
  - Add, rename, delete lists
  - Add, edit, delete cards within any list
  - Drag-and-drop reorder using HTML5 DnD API (no DnD library)
  - Vitest + React Testing Library test suite covering all CRUD operations

  === Phase 2: Node.js backend + SQLite ===
  - Express server in TypeScript on port 3001
  - SQLite database via better-sqlite3 (file: db/kanban.db)
  - DB schema: boards(id, name), lists(id, board_id, name, position),
               cards(id, list_id, title, description, position)
  - REST API:
      GET    /api/health
      GET    /api/boards/:id          — full board with lists and cards
      POST   /api/lists               — create list
      PATCH  /api/lists/:id           — rename or reposition
      DELETE /api/lists/:id
      POST   /api/cards               — create card
      PATCH  /api/cards/:id           — edit or move to different list
      DELETE /api/cards/:id
  - Frontend fetches from the API (no more localStorage)
  - Jest + supertest integration tests for all API endpoints

  === Phase 3: Docker deploy ===
  - Multi-stage Dockerfile: stage 1 builds frontend, stage 2 is Express server
    that serves the built frontend as static files from /public
  - docker-compose.yml: single `app` service, port 3001:3001,
    named volume `kanban-data` mounted at /app/db for SQLite persistence
  - GET /api/health returns {status: ok, uptime: <seconds>}
  - `podman-compose up --build -d` starts cleanly
  - `curl http://localhost:3001/api/health` returns 200
  - `curl http://localhost:3001/` serves the React app HTML

  Stack: React 18, TypeScript 5, Vite 5, Express 4, better-sqlite3, Vitest,
  @testing-library/react, Jest, supertest, Docker.

  === Phase 4: Documentation ===
  - Create a README.md to make sure that describes the application as a summary
  - Provide instructions in the README.md to build and deploy the application
  - Update the Claude.md including any agents and skills that may be required to mantain the project in the future"

 :project-dir nil

 :success-check
 "podman-compose up --build -d && sleep 8 && curl -sf http://localhost:3001/api/health && curl -sf http://localhost:3001/ | grep -q '<div id=\"root\"' && podman-compose down && test -f README.md && test -f CLAUDE.md"

 :constraints
 ["Work phase by phase: complete and test the frontend before starting the backend,
   complete and test the backend before writing the Dockerfile"
  "Run the relevant test suite at the end of every iteration — do not skip tests"
  "Run `npm run build` (frontend) or `tsc --noEmit` (server) each iteration to catch type errors"
  "Keep all board state in a single useKanban hook in the frontend"
  "Use a single Express app.ts entry point — do not split into many router files"]

 :anti-goals
 ["Do not install react-beautiful-dnd, dnd-kit, or any drag-and-drop library"
  "Do not use an ORM — use better-sqlite3 directly with prepared statements"
  "Do not add Redis, Postgres, or any dependency beyond what is listed in the objective"
  "Do not create shared utility files or helper modules used only in one place"
  "Do not leave TODO comments, unimplemented stubs, or placeholder routes"]

 :max-iterations      20
 :step-once?          false
 :generate-claude-md? true

 :fallback-model    "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001"
 :fallback-delay-ms 20000

 ;; Executor uses Haiku (fast, cheap) — builds the code
 :executor-model-config
 {:model-id    "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001"
  :temperature 0.2
  :max-tokens  8192}

 ;; Supervisor uses Sonnet — must reason across phases and steer correctly
 :supervisor-model-config
 {:model-id "claude-sonnet-4-6"
  :temperature 0.2
  :max-tokens  4096}}
